## Building an AI Chatbot in a React Website

AI chatbots are now a core part of modern web applications. They help users get instant answers, automate support, and improve engagement. In this guide, we will build a simple AI chatbot using React.

---

## 🚀 Step 1: Setting Up React Project

First, create a new React app:

```bash
npx create-react-app ai-chatbot
cd ai-chatbot
npm start
```

Now your React environment is ready.

---

## 💬 Step 2: Creating Chat UI

We will create a simple chat interface.

### Chat Component:

```javascript
import { useState } from "react";

export default function Chatbot() {
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState([]);
  const [input, setInput] = useState("");

  const sendMessage = async () => {
    if (!input.trim()) return;

    const newMessage = { role: "user", text: input };
    setMessages([...messages, newMessage]);
    setInput("");

    const botReply = await getAIResponse(input);

    setMessages((prev) => [
      ...prev,
      { role: "bot", text: botReply }
    ]);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <div>
        {messages.map((msg, i) => (
          <p key={i}>
            <strong>{msg.role}:</strong> {msg.text}
          </p>
        ))}
      </div>

      <input
        value={input}
        onChange={(e) => setInput(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="Ask something..."
      />

      <button onClick={sendMessage}>Send</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

## 🔌 Step 3: Connecting AI API

Now we connect our chatbot to an AI backend (like OpenAI API or any LLM API).

### Example API Function:

```javascript
async function getAIResponse(prompt) {
  const response = await fetch("https://api.example.com/chat", {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      "Content-Type": "application/json"
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({ message: prompt })
  });

  const data = await response.json();
  return data.reply;
}
```

---

## 🎨 Step 4: Improving UI/UX

A chatbot should be user-friendly and responsive.

### Add improvements:

- Scrollable chat window
- Typing indicator
- Message bubbles
- Mobile responsiveness

Example CSS idea:

```css
.chat-box {
  max-width: 400px;
  margin: auto;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  padding: 10px;
  border-radius: 10px;
}
```

---

## 🧠 Step 5: Adding Smart Features

To make your chatbot advanced:

- Store chat history in localStorage
- Add voice input using Web Speech API
- Use streaming responses for real-time typing effect

---

## 🌐 Use Cases

AI chatbots can be used in:

- Customer support websites
- E-commerce platforms
- Educational tools
- Personal assistants

---

## 🧩 Conclusion

Building an AI chatbot in React is easier than ever in 2026. With modern APIs and React hooks, you can create powerful conversational interfaces in just a few steps. Start simple, then gradually add intelligence and features.
